### Patient Management Service — Patient Endpoints
### Requires: REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
### Workflow: Login via identity-service first, paste the access_token into @token below.

@baseUrl    = http://localhost:8001
@token      = PASTE_YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@patientId  = PASTE_PATIENT_UUID_HERE
@mrn        = PASTE_MRN_HERE

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# POST /api/v1/patients  — Create a new patient
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1. Create patient — minimal required fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "first_name": "María",
  "last_name": "García",
  "date_of_birth": "1990-05-15",
  "gender": "female",
  "contact_info": {
    "phone_number": "+1-555-123-4567",
    "email": "maria.garcia@example.com"
  }
}

###

### 2. Create patient — full payload with all optional fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "first_name": "Carlos",
  "last_name": "Mendoza",
  "date_of_birth": "1985-11-20",
  "gender": "male",
  "marital_status": "married",
  "ssn_last_four": "5678",
  "national_id": "DOC-987654",
  "blood_type": "O+",
  "allergies": ["Penicillin", "Sulfa drugs"],
  "chronic_conditions": ["Hypertension", "Type 2 Diabetes"],
  "contact_info": {
    "phone_number": "+1-555-987-6543",
    "email": "carlos.mendoza@example.com",
    "secondary_phone": "+1-555-111-2222"
  },
  "address": {
    "street_line_1": "123 Main Street",
    "street_line_2": "Apt 4B",
    "city": "Miami",
    "state": "FL",
    "postal_code": "33101",
    "country": "US"
  },
  "emergency_contact": {
    "full_name": "Rosa Mendoza",
    "relationship": "Spouse",
    "phone_number": "+1-555-444-5555",
    "email": "rosa.mendoza@example.com"
  },
  "insurance_info": {
    "provider_name": "BlueCross BlueShield",
    "policy_number": "BCBS-2025-001",
    "group_number": "GRP-999",
    "subscriber_name": "Carlos Mendoza",
    "subscriber_relationship": "Self",
    "effective_date": "2025-01-01",
    "expiration_date": "2025-12-31"
  },
  "notes": "Patient prefers morning appointments."
}

###

### 3. Create patient — expect 409 Conflict (duplicate based on name + DOB)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "first_name": "María",
  "last_name": "García",
  "date_of_birth": "1990-05-15",
  "gender": "female",
  "contact_info": {
    "phone_number": "+1-555-123-4567"
  }
}

###

### 4. Create patient — expect 401 Unauthorized (missing token)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Test",
  "last_name": "NoAuth",
  "date_of_birth": "2000-01-01",
  "gender": "unknown",
  "contact_info": {
    "phone_number": "+1-555-000-0000"
  }
}

###

### 5. Create patient — expect 422 Unprocessable Entity (missing required contact_info)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "first_name": "Bad",
  "last_name": "Request",
  "date_of_birth": "1995-06-01",
  "gender": "female"
}


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GET /api/v1/patients/{patient_id}  — Get patient by UUID
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

###

### 6. Get patient by UUID — replace patientId variable at the top
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/{{patientId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 7. Get patient by UUID — expect 404 Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 8. Get patient by UUID — expect 401 Unauthorized (missing token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GET /api/v1/patients/mrn/{mrn}  — Get patient by MRN
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

###

### 9. Get patient by MRN — replace mrn variable at the top
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/mrn/{{mrn}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 10. Get patient by MRN — expect 404 Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/mrn/MRN-DOES-NOT-EXIST
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GET /api/v1/patients  — Search / list patients
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

###

### 11. Search all patients — default pagination (limit=20, offset=0)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 12. Search by first name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?first_name=María
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 13. Search by last name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?last_name=García
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 14. Search by first name + last name
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?first_name=Carlos&last_name=Mendoza
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 15. Search by date of birth
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?date_of_birth=1985-11-20
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 16. Search by MRN
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?mrn={{mrn}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 17. Filter by status (active | inactive | deceased | transferred)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?status=active
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 18. Search with custom pagination — page 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?limit=10&offset=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### 19. Combined search with all filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients?first_name=Carlos&status=active&limit=5&offset=0
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# PATCH /api/v1/patients/{patient_id}  — Partial update
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

###

### 20. Update patient contact info
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "contact_info": {
    "phone_number": "+1-555-999-8888",
    "email": "updated.email@example.com"
  }
}

###

### 21. Update patient allergies and notes
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "allergies": ["Penicillin", "Aspirin", "Latex"],
  "chronic_conditions": ["Hypertension"],
  "notes": "Updated note: patient transferred to specialist."
}

###

### 22. Update patient status to inactive
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "status": "inactive"
}

###

### 23. Update patient address
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "address": {
    "street_line_1": "456 New Ave",
    "city": "Orlando",
    "state": "FL",
    "postal_code": "32801",
    "country": "US"
  }
}

###

### 24. Update patient insurance info
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "insurance_info": {
    "provider_name": "Aetna",
    "policy_number": "AETNA-2026-777",
    "group_number": "GRP-200",
    "subscriber_name": "Carlos Mendoza",
    "subscriber_relationship": "Self",
    "effective_date": "2026-01-01",
    "expiration_date": "2026-12-31"
  }
}

###

### 25. Update patient — expect 404 Not Found
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "notes": "This patient does not exist."
}

###

### 26. Update patient — expect 403 Forbidden (receptionist role trying to update)
### Login as receptionist user and use that token here
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer RECEPTIONIST_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "notes": "Should be rejected."
}
